text.value:
 To make the NavBar disappear when the MangaFragment is showing, you can use a modifier on the NavBar composable that checks the current navigation route and only shows the NavBar if it's not on the "manga" route:

```kt
@Composable
fun NavBar() {

  // NavController and other NavBar code

  Box(
    modifier = Modifier
      .fillMaxSize()
      .background(color = MaterialTheme.colorScheme.surface)
  ) {

    AppNavigation(navController = navController)

    if (navController.currentDestination?.route != "manga") {
      BottomAppBar(modifier = Modifier.align(Alignment.BottomCenter)) {
        // NavBar items 
      }
    }

  }

}
```

So it will check if the current route is "manga", and if so, not show the BottomAppBar. Otherwise, it will display the NavBar as normal.
